                  <additions ana="high">
                     <p>The manuscript was written in 1724 by <name type="person" key="BjaPet001">Bjarni Pétursson</name> sýslumaður á <placeName>Skarði</placeName>
                        <locus from="1r" to="1r"/></p>
                     <p><locus from="1r" to="1r">1r</locus>, name: Jóhannes Jónsson</p>
                     <p><locus from="190v" to="190v">190v</locus>, name: Bjarni Bæringsson í
                           Ásgarði</p>
                     <p>According to P.E.Ó.-catalogue there are three hands</p>
                     <p>Added leaves: 1-4, 187, 215-234, 275-282</p>
                     <p>Added leaves, probably written in 1844: (see <locus from="1r" to="1r">1r</locus>)</p>
                     <p>Leaf <locus from="1r" to="1r">1r</locus> is a titlepage: Sagnabók af
                        allmörgum meiriháttar fornmönnum ... [maybe here it is Sólmundur farmer at
                        Mjóaból in Haukadalur, and his neighbour Jóhannes on Smyrlahóll (see Chris
                        Sanders' edition of Bevers saga)] </p>
                     <p>Fol. <locus from="1v" to="1v">1v</locus>: Innihald bókarinnar [table of contents]
                     </p>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding ana="decorative" contemporary="true">
